sections.History:
===â&euro;&lsaquo;[[Season 1]]===
â&euro;&lsaquo;The infamous [[Great Bastards]], legitimized bastard children of King [[Aegon IV Targaryen]], are mentioned in ''[[The Lineages and Histories of the Great Houses of the Seven Kingdoms]]''.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[A Golden Crown]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 3]]===
[[Catelyn Stark]] tells [[Talisa Stark]] that when [[Eddard Stark|her husband]]'s bastard [[Jon Snow]] became ill as an infant, she prayed to the [[Faith of the Seven|Seven]] to let him live, and in return promised to love him and ask her husband to legitimize him. Jon recovered, but Lady Stark did not stay true to her vow.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Dark Wings, Dark Words]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 4]]===
As a reward for [[Fall of Moat Cailin|liberating]] [[Moat Cailin]] from the [[ironborn]], [[Roose Bolton]] presents his bastard son [[Ramsay Bolton|Ramsay Snow]] with a decree of legitimacy. This makes him an official [[House Bolton|Bolton]] and Roose's heir, with the right to inherit his lands and titles when he dies. Ramsay is grateful for this, and promises to uphold his father's name and traditions.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Mountain and the Viper]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
